.\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1426, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Anything\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"injury\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"the nature\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just someone who likes to be prepared, so having that as a back-up, it's always there for me.\\\"\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1528, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just someone\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"a back-up\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Topping the podium twice in Japan propelled Summers-Newton from little-known newcomer to one of ParalympicsGB's headline acts.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.6527019983510165, \"rank\": 0.4784809266610371, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"Summers-Newton\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"little-known newcomer\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WithEllie Simmondsand Ellie Robinson having retired after the last Games, she is one of only two reigning champions in GB's current swimming squad, alongside S5 100m freestyle gold title holder Tully Kearney.\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Robinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ellie Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Robinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso